{"_id":"3JStySS9H7AssvgC","name":"Shield Proficiency","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/equipment/shields/wooden-shield.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You become trained in attacks made with shields, shield attachments, and shield adjustments that function as weapons. Whenever you gain a class feature that grants you expert or greater proficiency in certain weapons, you also gain that proficiency with shield attacks.</p>\n<p>Note that there is no proficiency requirement to be able to Raise a Shield or use the Shield Block reaction.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Everything Shields"},"traits":{"value":["general"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"upgrade","path":"data.martial.weapon-group-shield.rank","value":"@actor.data.data.martial.unarmed.rank"}],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.93,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2025-11-10T15:51:44.925Z","version":{"schema":0.93,"foundry":"13","system":"6.0.0"}}},"level":{"value":1},"featType":{"value":"general"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[]},"location":null},"ownership":{"default":0,"4mqS4QLqshw8WhsN":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.3.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1668741722041,"lastModifiedBy":"XyQNEFY9gmTDIpSd"},"schemaVersion":13}
{"_id":"4PWdIcwySe8Mrfau","name":"Shield Raft","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/spells/water-walk.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You can use your large shield to give yourself buoyancy. If you are wearing or wielding a heavy shield, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to Athletics checks to Swim on the surface of water (or other large body of liquid). This bonus does not apply to Swim checks made while underwater. If you are a master in Athletics, this circumstance bonus increases to +3.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Everything Shields"},"traits":{"value":["general","skill"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[{"key":"FlatModifier","label":"Shield Raft (swim on surface)","selector":"athletics","type":"circumstance","value":{"brackets":[{"end":4,"start":3,"value":3},{"end":2,"start":1,"value":2}],"field":"actor|data.skills.ath.rank"},"predicate":{"all":["action:swim"]}}],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.93,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2025-11-10T15:51:44.925Z","version":{"schema":0.93,"foundry":"13","system":"6.0.0"}}},"level":{"value":1},"featType":{"value":"skill"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"trained in Athletics"}]},"location":null},"ownership":{"default":0,"4mqS4QLqshw8WhsN":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.3.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1668741723922,"lastModifiedBy":"XyQNEFY9gmTDIpSd"},"schemaVersion":13}
{"_id":"91VTjIq2DU7CwhkL","name":"Shield Kite","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/spells/fly.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You are so in tune with the movement of air currents and the displacement of your body weight that you can manipulate the aerodynamics of your shield to glide through the air. When you are wielding a shield and you begin to fall, you may hold your shield overhead as a free action to slow your fall. You glide slowly toward the ground, 5 feet down and up to 25 feet forward through the air.</p>\n<p>On subsequent turns you may use an action to glide this way again. As long as you spend at least 1 action gliding each round and haven't yet reached the ground, you remain in the air at the end of your turn. You cannot Raise the Shield on the same turn that you use an action to glide in this way.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Everything Shields"},"traits":{"value":["general","skill"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.93,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2025-11-10T15:51:44.925Z","version":{"schema":0.93,"foundry":"13","system":"6.0.0"}}},"level":{"value":15},"featType":{"value":"skill"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"legendary in Acrobatics"}]},"location":null},"ownership":{"default":0,"4mqS4QLqshw8WhsN":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.3.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1668741719947,"lastModifiedBy":"XyQNEFY9gmTDIpSd"},"schemaVersion":13}
{"_id":"98eOxlZi4ft6GaT8","name":"Daunting Barricade","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/spells/shield.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You use your massive shield as much as a deterrent to aggression as you do to fight. When you are wielding a heavy shield and you attempt an Intimidation check to avoid a fight, such as Coercing potential enemies to stand down, you gain a +1 circumstance&nbsp; bonus to the check.</p>\n<p>If you have the Intimidating Prowess feat and its bonus would also apply when gaining the benefits of Daunting Barricade, increase the circumstance bonus of Daunting Barricade to +2, or +3 if your Strength score is 20 or higher.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Everything Shields"},"traits":{"value":["general","skill"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.93,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2025-11-10T15:51:44.925Z","version":{"schema":0.93,"foundry":"13","system":"6.0.0"}}},"level":{"value":7},"featType":{"value":"skill"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"master in Intimidation"}]},"location":null},"ownership":{"default":0,"4mqS4QLqshw8WhsN":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.3.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1668741696849,"lastModifiedBy":"XyQNEFY9gmTDIpSd"},"schemaVersion":13}
{"_id":"CEMkbRjibSZuOxdj","name":"Shield Flaunt","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/features/classes/perfected-form.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Requirements </strong>You have a shield raised.</p>\n<p><strong>Trigger</strong> A foe misses you because of the circumstance bonus to AC granted by your shield.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>After deflecting an attack with your shield, you flaunt your prowess in your opponent's face, or shout invectives to shame them for their failure. You attempt a @Compendium[pf2e.action-macros.EDLftLWLBefTFDtu]{Bon Mot: Diplomacy} against the triggering creature. The creature must still be within the range of your Bon Mot, but it loses the auditory and linguistic traits and gains the visual trait if you only taunt the creature with your shield.</p>\n<p>When used this way, the critical failure of Bon Mot becomes the following instead of its normal effects: \"Your taunt is so poorly executed you nearly lose your grip on your shield and have to quickly change your footing to catch your balance. You are @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.AJh5ex99aV6VTggg]{Flat-Footed} for 1 round.\"</p>"},"source":{"value":"Everything Shields"},"traits":{"value":["general","skill"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.93,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2025-11-10T15:51:44.925Z","version":{"schema":0.93,"foundry":"13","system":"6.0.0"}}},"level":{"value":7},"featType":{"value":"skill"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"reaction"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"master in Diplomacy"},{"value":"Bon Mot"}]},"location":null},"ownership":{"default":0,"4mqS4QLqshw8WhsN":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.3.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1668741715644,"lastModifiedBy":"XyQNEFY9gmTDIpSd"},"schemaVersion":13}
{"_id":"RIY8sXvzObBPMigH","name":"Light Shield Specialization","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/equipment/shields/buckler.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You gain access to @Compendium[everything-shields.everything-shields-actions.ThMUtWHNtRBSK4Cw]{Catch and Twist}, @Compendium[everything-shields.everything-shields-actions.1tKyIgAiewNqGaLz]{Disrupting Shield}, and @Compendium[everything-shields.everything-shields-actions.TqEAIf4HzI44LIoh]{Intercepting Shield}.&nbsp;</p>"},"source":{"value":"Everything Shields"},"traits":{"value":["general"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[{"allowDuplicate":false,"key":"GrantItem","uuid":"Compendium.everything-shields.everything-shields-actions.ThMUtWHNtRBSK4Cw"},{"allowDuplicate":false,"key":"GrantItem","uuid":"Compendium.everything-shields.everything-shields-actions.1tKyIgAiewNqGaLz"},{"allowDuplicate":false,"key":"GrantItem","uuid":"Compendium.everything-shields.everything-shields-actions.TqEAIf4HzI44LIoh"}],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.93,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2025-11-10T15:51:44.925Z","version":{"schema":0.93,"foundry":"13","system":"6.0.0"}}},"level":{"value":1},"featType":{"value":"general"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Shield Block"}]},"location":null},"ownership":{"default":0,"4mqS4QLqshw8WhsN":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.3.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1668741901970,"lastModifiedBy":"XyQNEFY9gmTDIpSd"},"schemaVersion":13}
{"_id":"SegO0RXJDDwwheB5","name":"Defensive Rider","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/spells/elephant-form.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You use your shield to prioritize deflecting blows that would knock you off your mount. If an attack or effect would cause you to fall off your mount while you are wielding a shield, such as an effect that would impose the prone condition on you, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to your AC or the appropriate saving throw (and the associated DC) against that attack or effect. If you would already receive a circumstance bonus because your shield is&nbsp; raised, this effect increases the bonus granted by your shield.</p>\n<p>If you are subjected to an effect that normally causes you to automatically be prone or otherwise be knocked off your mount, such as the creature ability Knockdown, you instead may attempt a Reflex save with the circumstance bonus listed above, negating the condition on a success or critical success. The DC for this save is the standard DC based on the creature's level.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Everything Shields"},"traits":{"value":["general","skill"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.93,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2025-11-10T15:51:44.925Z","version":{"schema":0.93,"foundry":"13","system":"6.0.0"}}},"level":{"value":2},"featType":{"value":"skill"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"expert in Nature"}]},"location":null},"ownership":{"default":0,"4mqS4QLqshw8WhsN":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.3.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1668741698756,"lastModifiedBy":"XyQNEFY9gmTDIpSd"},"schemaVersion":13}
{"_id":"Vb0D7CNFMd8C00nm","name":"Battle Gurney","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/spells/perfected-form.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Requirements </strong>you are wielding a heavy shield</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You quickly pull a wounded ally onto your shield and use it as a makeshift gurney to pull them to safety without worsening their wounds. Choose a willing or unconscious ally who is adjacent to you and is prone. You Stride, pulling the ally behind you 5 feet for each 5 feet of movement you take. You choose the path your ally takes as you pull them, but they must remain adjacent to you for the entire movement. This is forced movement for your ally.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Everything Shields"},"traits":{"value":["flourish","general","move","skill"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.93,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2025-11-10T15:51:44.925Z","version":{"schema":0.93,"foundry":"13","system":"6.0.0"}}},"level":{"value":7},"featType":{"value":"skill"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":"defensive"},"actions":{"value":1},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"master in Medicine"}]},"location":null},"ownership":{"default":0,"4mqS4QLqshw8WhsN":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.3.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1668741695280,"lastModifiedBy":"XyQNEFY9gmTDIpSd"},"schemaVersion":13}
{"_id":"VqyiFw1zOMIQ5tXz","name":"Anathematic Defense","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/features/classes/anathema(cleric).webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You have trained relentlessly to defend against the attacks of your ancient foes. When you use the Shield Block reaction to block an attack from an enemy whose alignment is opposite your deity's alignment, your shield's Hardness is increased by 2. For example this would apply if your deity is lawful good and you defend&nbsp; against an attack from a chaotic evil creature.</p>\n<p>If your deity is&nbsp; neutral on one axis, then this works against enemies who are also neutral on that axis and opposed on the other. For example if your deity is neutral evil, then this applies against enemies who are neutral good. If your deity is lawful neutral, then this applies against enemies who are chaotic neutral.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Everything Shields"},"traits":{"value":["general","skill"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[{"key":"ChoiceSet","label":"Anathematic Defense Alignment","prompt":"Which alignment is your primary deity?","adjustName":true,"flag":"everything-shields.anathematic-defense-alignment","choices":[{"label":"Lawful Good","value":" lawful-good"},{"label":"Neutral Good","value":"neutral-good"},{"label":"Chaotic Good","value":"chaotic-good"},{"label":"Lawful Neutral","value":"lawful-neutral"},{"label":"Chaotic Neutral","value":"chaotic-neutral"},{"label":"Lawful Evil","value":"lawful-evil"},{"label":"Neutral Evil","value":"neutral-evil"},{"label":"Chaotic Evil","value":"chaotic-evil"}]},{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","mode":"add","path":"data.attributes.shield.hardness","value":2,"selector":"all","predicate":{"all":["anathematic-defense"]},"phase":"beforeDerived"},{"key":"RollOption","domain":"all","option":"anathematic-defense","toggleable":true}],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.93,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2025-11-10T15:51:44.925Z","version":{"schema":0.93,"foundry":"13","system":"6.0.0"}}},"level":{"value":7},"featType":{"value":"skill"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"master in Religion"},{"value":"You follow a non-neutral deity"}]},"location":null},"ownership":{"default":0,"4mqS4QLqshw8WhsN":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.3.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1668741693751,"lastModifiedBy":"XyQNEFY9gmTDIpSd"},"schemaVersion":13}
{"_id":"X5jCau51AGAINemX","name":"Shield Tinker","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/spells/community-repair.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>As a master craftsman you often find small ways to tweak your own equipment to give yourself an edge. You may apply two adjustments to your shields instead of one. The complexity of working with these adjustments prevents others from using shields that you have adjusted this way, unless they also have this feat.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Everything Shields"},"traits":{"value":["general","skill"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.93,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2025-11-10T15:51:44.925Z","version":{"schema":0.93,"foundry":"13","system":"6.0.0"}}},"level":{"value":7},"featType":{"value":"skill"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"master in Crafting"}]},"location":null},"ownership":{"default":0,"4mqS4QLqshw8WhsN":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.3.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1668741728440,"lastModifiedBy":"XyQNEFY9gmTDIpSd"},"schemaVersion":13}
{"_id":"XYykSONot5Rrznny","name":"Feinted Shield Charge","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/spells/mislead.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Requirements </strong>you are wielding a shield</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You are adept at charging toward an opponent just menacingly enough to convince them to square off with you, and that's when you break away. Choose a target that you can see. You Stride&nbsp; toward your target, then make a Deception check to <span data-pf2-action=\"feint\" data-pf2-glyph=\"F\">Feint</span> as long as you are&nbsp;within 20 feet of the target at the end of your Stride, ignoring the normal requirement that you be within melee reach of the target.</p>\n<p>Instead of the normal effects of a Feint, on a success the target is&nbsp; @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.AJh5ex99aV6VTggg]{Flat-Footed} to the next attack that an ally attempts against the target. On a critical success, the target is flat-footed to all attacks by your allies until the start of your next turn. The critical failure effects remain the same.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Everything Shields"},"traits":{"value":["general","skill"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.93,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2025-11-10T15:51:44.925Z","version":{"schema":0.93,"foundry":"13","system":"6.0.0"}}},"level":{"value":7},"featType":{"value":"skill"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":"offensive"},"actions":{"value":2},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"master in Deception"}]},"location":null},"ownership":{"default":0,"4mqS4QLqshw8WhsN":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.3.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1668741700769,"lastModifiedBy":"XyQNEFY9gmTDIpSd"},"schemaVersion":13}
{"_id":"dAZFOqjM1nKciIsO","name":"Practiced Materials","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/features/classes/advanced-alchemy.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Requirements </strong>You are wielding a shield in one or more hands.</p>\n<p><strong>Frequency </strong>once per minute</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You have become so accustomed to wielding a shield while casting your spells that you can occasionally reach quickly into your component pouch with your shield hand. You do not need a free hand to supply material components until the end of your turn.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Everything Shields"},"traits":{"value":["general","skill"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.93,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2025-11-10T15:51:44.925Z","version":{"schema":0.93,"foundry":"13","system":"6.0.0"}}},"level":{"value":2},"featType":{"value":"skill"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"free"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"expert in Arcana or Occultism"}]},"location":null},"ownership":{"default":0,"4mqS4QLqshw8WhsN":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.3.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1668741708387,"lastModifiedBy":"XyQNEFY9gmTDIpSd"},"schemaVersion":13}
{"_id":"eRJYP5zGTcjVu2sH","name":"Heavy Shield Specialization","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/equipment/shields/tower-shield.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You gain access to @Compendium[everything-shields.everything-shields-actions.FTSBSxOuc2WaHWIN]{Bulwark Shield} and @Compendium[everything-shields.everything-shields-actions.PryAVFCjglp4YXXv]{Shoving Shield}.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Everything Shields"},"traits":{"value":["general"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[{"allowDuplicate":false,"key":"GrantItem","uuid":"Compendium.everything-shields.everything-shields-actions.FTSBSxOuc2WaHWIN"},{"allowDuplicate":false,"key":"GrantItem","uuid":"Compendium.everything-shields.everything-shields-actions.PryAVFCjglp4YXXv"}],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.93,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2025-11-10T15:51:44.925Z","version":{"schema":0.93,"foundry":"13","system":"6.0.0"}}},"level":{"value":1},"featType":{"value":"general"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Shield Block"}]},"location":null},"ownership":{"default":0,"4mqS4QLqshw8WhsN":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.3.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1668741702975,"lastModifiedBy":"XyQNEFY9gmTDIpSd"},"schemaVersion":13}
{"_id":"fbIjVJ473J1ffauK","name":"Medium Shield Specialization","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/equipment/shields/steel-shield.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You gain access to @Compendium[everything-shields.everything-shields-actions.hEAs9KLDWgpXIOzi]{Aiding Shield} and @Compendium[everything-shields.everything-shields-actions.Rqh2hHC1ZvQwnust]{Covering Shield}.&nbsp;</p>"},"source":{"value":"Everything Shields"},"traits":{"value":["general"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[{"allowDuplicate":false,"key":"GrantItem","uuid":"Compendium.everything-shields.everything-shields-actions.hEAs9KLDWgpXIOzi"},{"allowDuplicate":false,"key":"GrantItem","uuid":"Compendium.everything-shields.everything-shields-actions.hEAs9KLDWgpXIOzi"}],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.93,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2025-11-10T15:51:44.925Z","version":{"schema":0.93,"foundry":"13","system":"6.0.0"}}},"level":{"value":1},"featType":{"value":"general"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"Shield Block"}]},"location":null},"ownership":{"default":0,"4mqS4QLqshw8WhsN":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.3.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1668741906479,"lastModifiedBy":"XyQNEFY9gmTDIpSd"},"schemaVersion":13}
{"_id":"gsnjScbhsmWVyvef","name":"Shield Smash","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/equipment/shields/specific-shields/reflecting-shield.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p><strong>Requirements </strong>You are wielding a shield.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You quickly raise up your shield and bash your target, dazing them, and leaving yourself open for a moment. Choose an adjacent foe and attempt an Athletics check against the target's Reflex DC.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The target is&nbsp; @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.e1XGnhKNSQIm5IXg]{Stupefied} 2 for 1 minute, and you @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.xjGwis0uaC2305pm]{Raise a Shield}. The target can spend an action with the concentrate trait to end this effect after 1 round has passed.</p>\n<p><strong>Success </strong>The target is stupefied 1 for 1 round, and you Raise the Shield.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> You Raise the Shield.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> You lose your grip on the shield, or its fastenings come loose. You @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.wQYmDStjdjn0I26t]{Release} the shield.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Everything Shields"},"traits":{"value":["attack","general","manipulate","skill"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.93,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2025-11-10T15:51:44.925Z","version":{"schema":0.93,"foundry":"13","system":"6.0.0"}}},"level":{"value":2},"featType":{"value":"skill"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"action"},"actionCategory":{"value":"offensive"},"actions":{"value":2},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"expert in Athletics"}]},"location":null},"ownership":{"default":0,"4mqS4QLqshw8WhsN":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.3.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1668741726354,"lastModifiedBy":"XyQNEFY9gmTDIpSd"},"schemaVersion":13}
{"_id":"lk06dFWUyuQQVfwk","name":"Seasoned Shield Warrior","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/spells/song-of-marching.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You are so accustomed to traveling with your shield ready to go at a moment's notice, you no longer even notice its bulk. If you are wearing or carrying only one shield, treat the bulk of that shield as 2 less for the purpose of calculating your encumbrance. If the shield has 2 or less bulk, its bulk is treated as negligible. If you are&nbsp; wearing or carrying more than one shield, choose one shield to receive this bonus. This does not change the actual bulk or the category of the shield.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Everything Shields"},"traits":{"value":["general","skill"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","path":"data.attributes.bonusLimitBulk","mode":"add","value":2},{"key":"ActiveEffectLike","path":"data.attributes.bonusEncumbranceBulk","mode":"add","value":2}],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.93,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2025-11-10T15:51:44.925Z","version":{"schema":0.93,"foundry":"13","system":"6.0.0"}}},"level":{"value":1},"featType":{"value":"skill"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"trained in Survival"}]},"location":null},"ownership":{"default":0,"4mqS4QLqshw8WhsN":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.3.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1668741712194,"lastModifiedBy":"XyQNEFY9gmTDIpSd"},"schemaVersion":13}
{"_id":"pnzbXwoyBUhMTmMd","name":"Shield Historian","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/equipment/held-items/book-of-lingering-blaze.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You have made a study of shields and their usage historically and in different cultures and societies. When you attempt a check to Impersonate a person or role that typically carries a shield, whether for functional use or decoratively, you may use Society instead of Deception. If you have at least 1 hour to prepare, you gain a +1 circumstance bonus on this check.</p>\n<p>Additionally when you attempt a Recall Knowledge check related to shields, shield usage, or to identify any creature who is wielding a shield, you may use Society for the check regardless of what the normal skill would be, and you gain a +1 circumstance bonus on the&nbsp; check.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Everything Shields"},"traits":{"value":["general","skill"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.93,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2025-11-10T15:51:44.925Z","version":{"schema":0.93,"foundry":"13","system":"6.0.0"}}},"level":{"value":2},"featType":{"value":"skill"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"expert in Society"}]},"location":null},"ownership":{"default":0,"4mqS4QLqshw8WhsN":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.3.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1668741717658,"lastModifiedBy":"XyQNEFY9gmTDIpSd"},"schemaVersion":13}
{"_id":"qCjpFxUeoXg9ttMt","name":"Shield Drum","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/equipment/held-items/folding_drums.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You have mastered the art of using your shield as if it were a drum, finding different tones across the face of the shield, and striking it with your hand or weapon to make music. While you are wielding a shield, it counts as a musical instrument. If your shield has a shield potency rune inscribed on it, it counts as a @Compendium[pf2e.equipment-srd.bAfyWCvgsYDyw3ff]{Maestro's Instrument (Lesser)}. If the shield potency rune is +2, it counts as a @Compendium[pf2e.equipment-srd.3mprh9aZ670HfNhT]{Maestro's Instrument (Moderate)}, and if the shield potency rune is +3, it&nbsp; counts as a @Compendium[pf2e.equipment-srd.rlDIbl6EQYXQpWVs]{Maestro's Instrument (Greater)}.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Everything Shields"},"traits":{"value":["general","skill"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.93,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2025-11-10T15:51:44.925Z","version":{"schema":0.93,"foundry":"13","system":"6.0.0"}}},"level":{"value":7},"featType":{"value":"skill"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"master in Performance"}]},"location":null},"ownership":{"default":0,"4mqS4QLqshw8WhsN":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.3.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1668741714065,"lastModifiedBy":"XyQNEFY9gmTDIpSd"},"schemaVersion":13}
{"_id":"z4YomuQEkLT8MdPp","name":"Screening Shield","type":"feat","img":"systems/pf2e/icons/spells/steal-shadow.webp","effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"flags":{},"system":{"description":{"value":"<p>You use the size of your shield to cover the movements of your other hand. When you @Compendium[pf2e.actionspf2e.ijZ0DDFpMkWqaShd]{Palm an Object} while you are wielding a shield and your other hand is free, you may palm larger objects than you normally could. If you are wielding a light shield, you may Palm an Object up to light bulk, and if you are wielding a medium or heavy shield you may Palm an Object up to 1 bulk.</p>"},"source":{"value":"Everything Shields"},"traits":{"value":["general","skill"],"rarity":"common","custom":""},"rules":[],"slug":null,"schema":{"version":0.93,"lastMigration":{"datetime":"2025-11-10T15:51:44.925Z","version":{"schema":0.93,"foundry":"13","system":"6.0.0"}}},"level":{"value":7},"featType":{"value":"skill"},"onlyLevel1":false,"maxTakable":1,"actionType":{"value":"passive"},"actionCategory":{"value":""},"actions":{"value":null},"prerequisites":{"value":[{"value":"master in Thievery"}]},"location":null},"ownership":{"default":0,"4mqS4QLqshw8WhsN":3},"_stats":{"systemId":"pf2e","systemVersion":"4.3.4","coreVersion":"10.290","createdTime":null,"modifiedTime":1668741710321,"lastModifiedBy":"XyQNEFY9gmTDIpSd"},"schemaVersion":13}
